obj_root_law_sections_1:
  sectionId (36189)
  sectionNo (1)
  orderNo 1
  title `Short title and commencement.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_1_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_24_32_00002_195649_1517807321201&sectionId=36189&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_24_32_00002_195649_1517807321201
obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line `(1) This Act may be called the River Boards Act, 1956.`
  line
  line `(2) It shall come into force on such date^1`
  line `as the Central Government may, by notification in the`
  line `Official Gazette, appoint.`
obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes:
  string
  line `1 15th May, 1957, vide notification No. EL-I-452 (17)/57, dated 11th May, 1957, see Gazette of India, Extraordinary, Part II,`
  line `sec. 1.`
  line `1st October, 1973, vide Reg. 7 of 1963, s. 3 and the First Schedule in respect of Pondicherry.`
  line `1st July 1965, vide Reg. 6 of 1963, s. 2 and the First Schedule extended to and brought into force in respect of the Dadra and`
  line `Nagar Haveli.`
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (36190)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title `Declaration as to expediency of control by Central Government.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_24_32_00002_195649_1517807321201&sectionId=36190&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_24_32_00002_195649_1517807321201
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `It is hereby declared that it is`
  line `expedient in the public interest that the Central Government should take under its control the regulation`
  line `and development of inter-State rivers and river valleys, to the extent hereinafter provided.`
obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (36191)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 3
  title Definitions.
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_24_32_00002_195649_1517807321201&sectionId=36191&sectionno=3&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_24_32_00002_195649_1517807321201
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `In this Act, unless the context otherwise requires,--`
  line
  line `(a) "Board" means a River Board establishment under section 4;`
  line
  line `(b) "Governments interested", in relation to a Board, means the Governments of those States`
  line `which, in the opinion of the Central Government, are likely to be interested in, or affected by, the`
  line `functions of the Board under this Act;`
  line
  line `(c) "member" means a member of a Board and includes its Chairman;`
  line
  line `(d) "prescribed" means prescribed by rules made under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (36192)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 4
  title `Establishment of Boards.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_24_32_00002_195649_1517807321201&sectionId=36192&sectionno=4&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_24_32_00002_195649_1517807321201
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government may, on a request received in this behalf`
  line `from a State Government or otherwise, by notification in the Official Gazette, establish a River Board for`
  line `advising the Governments interested in relation to such matters concerning the regulation or development`
  line `of an inter-State river or river valley or any specified part thereof and for performing such other functions`
  line `as may be specified in the notification, and different Boards may be established for different inter-State`
  line `rivers or river valleys:`
  line
  line `Provided that no such notification shall be except after consultation with the Governments interested`
  line `with respect to the proposal to establish the Board, the persons to be appointed as members thereof and`
  line `the functions which the Board may be empowered to perform.`
  line
  line `(2) A Board may be established under such name as may be specified in the notification under`
  line `sub-section (1).`
  line
  line `(3) Every Board so established shall be a body corporate having perpetual succession and a common`
  line `seal, and shall by the said name sue and be sued.`
  line
  line `(4) Every Board shall exercise its jurisdiction within such limits of the river (including its tributaries,`
  line `if any) or river valley as may be specified in the notification under sub-section (1) and the area so`
  line `specified shall be called the area of operation of the Board.`
obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  sectionId (36193)
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 5
  title `Composition of Board.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_24_32_00002_195649_1517807321201&sectionId=36193&sectionno=5&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_24_32_00002_195649_1517807321201
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Board shall consist of a Chairman and such other members as`
  line `the Central Government thinks fit to appoint.`
  line
  line `(2) A person shall not be qualified for appointment as a member unless, in the opinion of the Central`
  line `Government, he has special knowledge and experience in irrigation, electrical engineering flood control,`
  line `navigation, water conservation, soil conservation administration or finance.`
obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  sectionId (36194)
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 6
  title `Terms and conditions of service of members.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_24_32_00002_195649_1517807321201&sectionId=36194&sectionno=6&orderno=6&orgactid=AC_CEN_24_32_00002_195649_1517807321201
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line `(1) A member shall, unless his appointment is`
  line `terminated earlier by the Central Government, hold office for such period as may be notified in this behalf`
  line `by the Central Government in the Official Gazette, and shall, on the expiry of the term of his office be`
  line `eligible for re-appointment.`
  line
  line `(2) A member may resign his office by writing under his hand addressed to the Central Government,`
  line `but he shall continue in office until the appointment of his successor is notified in the Official Gazette.`
  line
  line `(3) A casual vacancy created by the resignation of a member under sub-section (2) or for any other`
  line `reason shall be filled by fresh appointment.`
  line
  line `(4) A member may be appointed either as a whole-time or part-time member as the Central`
  line `Government thinks fit.`
  line
  line `(5) The terms and conditions of service of the Chairman and other members shall be such as may be`
  line prescribed.
obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_7:
  sectionId (36195)
  sectionNo (7)
  orderNo 7
  title `Temporary absence of any member.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_24_32_00002_195649_1517807321201&sectionId=36195&sectionno=7&orderno=7&orgactid=AC_CEN_24_32_00002_195649_1517807321201
obj_root_law_sections_7_content:
  string
  line `If any member is by infirmity or otherwise rendered`
  line `temporarily incapable of carrying out his duties or is absent on leave or otherwise in circumstances not`
  line `involving the vacation of his appointment, the Central Government may appoint another person to act in`
  line `his place.`
obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_8:
  sectionId (36196)
  sectionNo (8)
  orderNo 8
  title `Meetings of Board.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_24_32_00002_195649_1517807321201&sectionId=36196&sectionno=8&orderno=8&orgactid=AC_CEN_24_32_00002_195649_1517807321201
obj_root_law_sections_8_content:
  string
  line `The Board shall meet at such times and places and shall observe such rules`
  line `of procedure in regard to the transaction of business at its meetings as may be provided by regulations`
  line `made under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_9:
  sectionId (36197)
  sectionNo (9)
  orderNo 9
  title `Vacancy in Board, etc., not to invalidate acts or proceedings.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_24_32_00002_195649_1517807321201&sectionId=36197&sectionno=9&orderno=9&orgactid=AC_CEN_24_32_00002_195649_1517807321201
obj_root_law_sections_9_content:
  string
  line `No act or proceeding of the`
  line `Board shall be deemed to be invalid by reason only of the existence of any vacancy in the Board or any`
  line `defect in the appointment of a member thereof.`
obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_10:
  sectionId (36198)
  sectionNo (10)
  orderNo 10
  title `Appointment of advisory committee.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_24_32_00002_195649_1517807321201&sectionId=36198&sectionno=10&orderno=10&orgactid=AC_CEN_24_32_00002_195649_1517807321201
obj_root_law_sections_10_content:
  string
  line `The Board may, from time to time, appoint one or more`
  line `advisory committee or committees for the purpose of enabling it to carry out of its functions under this`
  line Act.
obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_11:
  sectionId (36199)
  sectionNo (11)
  orderNo 11
  title `Temporary association of persons with Board for particular purposes.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_11_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_24_32_00002_195649_1517807321201&sectionId=36199&sectionno=11&orderno=11&orgactid=AC_CEN_24_32_00002_195649_1517807321201
obj_root_law_sections_11_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Board may`
  line `associate with itself in such manner and for such purposes as may be determined by regulations made`
  line `under this Act any person whose assistance or advice it may desire in performing any of its functions`
  line `under this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) A person associated with the Board under sub-section (1) for any purpose shall have a right to`
  line `take part in the discussions of the Board relevant to that purpose, but shall not have a right to vote at a`
  line `meeting of the Board, and shall not be a member for any other purpose.`
obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_12:
  sectionId (36200)
  sectionNo (12)
  orderNo 12
  title `Staff of Board.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_12_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_24_32_00002_195649_1517807321201&sectionId=36200&sectionno=12&orderno=12&orgactid=AC_CEN_24_32_00002_195649_1517807321201
obj_root_law_sections_12_content:
  string
  line `Subject to such rules as may by the Central Government in this behalf, the`
  line `Board may, for the purpose of enabling it to efficiently perform its functions or exercise its powers under`
  line `this Act, appoint such officers as it may think fit and determine their functions and terms and conditions`
  line `of service.`
obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_13:
  sectionId (36201)
  sectionNo (13)
  orderNo 13
  title `Matters in respect of which a Board may be authorised to tender advice.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_13_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_24_32_00002_195649_1517807321201&sectionId=36201&sectionno=13&orderno=13&orgactid=AC_CEN_24_32_00002_195649_1517807321201
obj_root_law_sections_13_content:
  string
  line `A Board may be`
  line `empowered under sub-section (1) of section 14 to perform all or any of the following functions,`
  line `namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) advising the Governments interested on any matter concerning the regulation or development`
  line `of any specified inter-State river or river valley within its area of operation and in particular, advising them in relation to the co-ordination of their activities with a view to resolve conflicts among them`
  line `and to achieve maximum results in respect of the measures undertaken by them in the inter-State river`
  line `or river valley for the purpose of--`
  line
  line `(i) conservation, control and optimum utilisation of water resources of the inter-State river;`
  line
  line `(ii) promotion and operation of schemes for irrigation, water supply or drainage;`
  line
  line `(iii) promotion and operation of schemes for the development of hydro-electric power;`
  line
  line `(iv) promotion and operation of schemes for flood control;`
  line
  line `(v) promotion and control of navigation;`
  line
  line `(vi) promotion of afforestation and control of soil erosion;`
  line
  line `(vii) prevention of pollution of the waters of the inter-State river;`
  line
  line `(viii) such other matters as may be prescribed;`
  line
  line `(b) preparing schemes, including multi-purpose schemes, for the purpose of regulating or`
  line `developing the inter-State river or river valley and advising the Governments interested to undertake`
  line `measures for executing the scheme prepared by the Board;`
  line
  line `(c) allocating among the Governments interested the costs of executing any scheme prepared by`
  line `the Board and of works undertaken in the execution of the scheme;`
  line
  line `(d) watching the progress of the measures undertaken by the Governments interested;`
  line
  line `(e) any other matter which is supplemental, incidental or consequential to any of the above`
  line functions.
obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_14:
  sectionId (36202)
  sectionNo (14)
  orderNo 14
  title `Functions of Board.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_14_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_24_32_00002_195649_1517807321201&sectionId=36202&sectionno=14&orderno=14&orgactid=AC_CEN_24_32_00002_195649_1517807321201
obj_root_law_sections_14_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government, after consultation with the Governments`
  line `interested, may, by notification in the Official Gazette, empower the Board to perform all or such of the`
  line `functions under section 13 as may be specified in the notification.`
  line
  line `(2) The Board shall exercise its powers and perform all the functions which it is empowered to do by`
  line `or under this Act within its area of operation.`
  line
  line `(3) In performing its functions under this Act, the Board shall consult the Governments interested at`
  line `all stages and endeavour to secure, as far as may be practicable, agreement among such Governments.`
obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_15:
  sectionId (36203)
  sectionNo (15)
  orderNo 15
  title `Preparation of schemes by Board and their execution.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_15_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_24_32_00002_195649_1517807321201&sectionId=36203&sectionno=15&orderno=15&orgactid=AC_CEN_24_32_00002_195649_1517807321201
obj_root_law_sections_15_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where any Board has been`
  line `empowered to perform functions under clause (b) of section 13, the Board may, from time to time,`
  line `prepare schemes, not inconsistent with its functions under this Act, for the purpose of regulating or`
  line `developing any inter-State river or river valley within its area of operation.`
  line
  line `(2) After preparing any such scheme, the Board shall consult the Governments interested and the`
  line `Central Government in respect of the scheme and after considering their suggestions, if any, the Board`
  line `may confirm, modify or reject the scheme.`
  line
  line `(3) The scheme as confirmed or modified under sub-section (2) shall thereupon become final and`
  line `shall be called the approved scheme.`
  line
  line `(4) Before any scheme is approved, the Board shall take into account the costs likely to be incurred in`
  line `undertaking measures for executing the scheme and in maintaining any works to be undertaken in the`
  line `execution of the scheme and the costs shall be allocated among the Governments interested in such`
  line `proportion as may be agreed or, in default of agreement, as may be determined by the Board having`
  line `regard to the benefits which will be received from the scheme by them.`
  line
  line `(5) Every approved scheme shall be forwarded to the Governments interested and the Board may`
  line `advise them to undertake measures for executing the scheme and a copy of the approved scheme shall`
  line `also be forwarded to the Central Government.`
  line
  line `(6) The Central Government may, on a request received in this behalf from any Government`
  line `interested or otherwise, assist the Governments interested in taking such steps as may be necessary for the`
  line `execution of the scheme.`
obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_16:
  sectionId (36204)
  sectionNo (16)
  orderNo 16
  title `General Powers of Board.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_16_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_24_32_00002_195649_1517807321201&sectionId=36204&sectionno=16&orderno=16&orgactid=AC_CEN_24_32_00002_195649_1517807321201
obj_root_law_sections_16_content:
  string
  line `For the purpose of efficiently performing its functions under this`
  line `Act, every Board may, within its area of operation,--`
  line
  line `(a) acquire, hold and dispose of such property, both movable and immovable, as it deems`
  line necessary;
  line
  line `(b) undertake such preliminary investigation or surveys or other measures as it deems necessary;`
  line
  line `(c) inspect or cause to be inspected any works undertaken by any Government interested`
  line `concerning the regulation or development of the inter-State river or river valley;`
  line
  line `(d) conduct and co-ordinate research or various aspects of the conservation, regulation or`
  line `utilisation of water resources, such as water power generation, irrigation, navigation, flood control,`
  line `soil conservation, land use and connected structural and design features;`
  line
  line `(e) collect such topographical, meteorological, hydrological and sub-soil water data as it deems`
  line necessary;
  line
  line `(f) publish statistics or other information relating to the various aspects of the regulation or`
  line `development of the inter-State river or river valley;`
  line
  line `(g) require any Government interested to furnish such information as the Board may require in`
  line `relation to--`
  line
  line `(i) the measures undertaken by that Government for the regulation or development of the`
  line `inter-State river or river valley;`
  line
  line `(ii) the topographical, meteorological, hydrological and sub-soil water data;`
  line
  line `(iii) such other matters as may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_17:
  sectionId (36205)
  sectionNo (17)
  orderNo 17
  title `Payment to Board.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_17_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_24_32_00002_195649_1517807321201&sectionId=36205&sectionno=17&orderno=17&orgactid=AC_CEN_24_32_00002_195649_1517807321201
obj_root_law_sections_17_content:
  string
  line `The Central Government may, after due appropriation made by Parliament`
  line `by law in this behalf, pay to the Board in each financial year such sums as the Central Government may`
  line `consider necessary for the performance of the functions of the Board under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_18:
  sectionId (36206)
  sectionNo (18)
  orderNo 18
  title `Fund of Board.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_18_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_24_32_00002_195649_1517807321201&sectionId=36206&sectionno=18&orderno=18&orgactid=AC_CEN_24_32_00002_195649_1517807321201
obj_root_law_sections_18_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Board shall have its own fund, and all sums which may, from time to`
  line `time, be paid to it by the Central Government or a State Government and all other receipts of the Board`
  line `shall be carried to the fund of the Board and all payments by the Board shall be made therefrom.`
  line
  line `(2) The Board may expend such sums as it thinks fit for performing its functions under this Act, and`
  line `such sums shall be treated as expenditure payable out of the fund of the Board.`
obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_19:
  sectionId (36207)
  sectionNo (19)
  orderNo 19
  title Budget.
  content obj_root_law_sections_19_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_24_32_00002_195649_1517807321201&sectionId=36207&sectionno=19&orderno=19&orgactid=AC_CEN_24_32_00002_195649_1517807321201
obj_root_law_sections_19_content:
  string
  line `The Board shall prepare, in such form and at such time each year as may be prescribed,`
  line `a budget in respect of the financial year next ensuing showing the estimated receipts and expenditure, and`
  line `copies thereof shall be forwarded to the Central Government and the Governments interested.`
obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_20:
  sectionId (36208)
  sectionNo (20)
  orderNo 20
  title `Annual report.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_20_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_24_32_00002_195649_1517807321201&sectionId=36208&sectionno=20&orderno=20&orgactid=AC_CEN_24_32_00002_195649_1517807321201
obj_root_law_sections_20_content:
  string
  line `The Board shall prepare, in such form and at such time each year as may be`
  line `prescribed, an annual report giving a true and full account of its activities during the previous year and`
  line `copies thereof shall be forwarded to the Central Government and the Governments interested; and the`
  line `Central Government shall cause every such report to be laid before both Houses of Parliament.`
obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_21:
  sectionId (36209)
  sectionNo (21)
  orderNo 21
  title `Accounts and audit.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_21_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_24_32_00002_195649_1517807321201&sectionId=36209&sectionno=21&orderno=21&orgactid=AC_CEN_24_32_00002_195649_1517807321201
obj_root_law_sections_21_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Board shall cause to be maintained such books of account and`
  line `other books in relation to its accounts in such form and in such manner as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(2) The accounts of the Board shall be audited at such time and in such manner as may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_22:
  sectionId (36210)
  sectionNo (22)
  orderNo 22
  title Arbitration.
  content obj_root_law_sections_22_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_24_32_00002_195649_1517807321201&sectionId=36210&sectionno=22&orderno=22&orgactid=AC_CEN_24_32_00002_195649_1517807321201
obj_root_law_sections_22_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where any dispute or difference arises between two or more Government`
  line `interested with respect to--`
  line
  line `(a) any advice tendered by the Board under this Act;`
  line
  line `(b) any measurers undertaken by any Government interested in pursuance of any advice tendered`
  line `by the Board;`
  line
  line `(c) the refusal or neglect of any Government interested to undertake any measurers in pursuance`
  line `of any advice tendered by the Board;`
  line
  line `(d) the sharing of benefits or financial liabilities arising out of any advice tendered by the Board;`
  line
  line `(e) any other matter covered by this Act or touching or arising out of it,`
  line
  line `any of the Governments interested may, in such form and in such manner as may be prescribed, refer the`
  line `matter in dispute to arbitration.`
  line
  line `(2) The arbitrator shall be person to be appointed in this behalf by the Chief Justice of India from`
  line `among persons who are, or have been, Judges of the Supreme Court or are Judges of a High Court.`
  line
  line `(3) The arbitrator may appoint two or more persons as assessors to assist him in the proceeding before`
  line him.
  line
  line `(4) The decision of the arbitrator shall be final and binding on the parties to the dispute and shall be`
  line `given effect to by them.`
  line
  line `(5) Nothing in the Arbitration Act, 1940 (10 of 1940), shall apply to arbitrations under this section.`
obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_23:
  sectionId (36211)
  sectionNo (23)
  orderNo 23
  title `Returns and reports.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_23_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_24_32_00002_195649_1517807321201&sectionId=36211&sectionno=23&orderno=23&orgactid=AC_CEN_24_32_00002_195649_1517807321201
obj_root_law_sections_23_content:
  string
  line `The Board shall furnish to the Central Government such returns,`
  line `statistics, accounts and other information with respect to its fund or activities as the Central Government`
  line `may from time to time require.`
obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_24:
  sectionId (36212)
  sectionNo (24)
  orderNo 24
  title `Delegation of powers.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_24_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_24_32_00002_195649_1517807321201&sectionId=36212&sectionno=24&orderno=24&orgactid=AC_CEN_24_32_00002_195649_1517807321201
obj_root_law_sections_24_content:
  string
  line `The Board may, by general or special order in writing, delegate to the`
  line `chairman or any other member of any officer of the Board, subject to such conditions and limitations, if`
  line `any, as may be specified in the order, such of its powers and functions under this Act as it may deem`
  line `necessary for the efficient running of the day-to day administration of the Board.`
obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_25:
  sectionId (36213)
  sectionNo (25)
  orderNo 25
  title `Members and officers of Board to be public servants.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_25_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_24_32_00002_195649_1517807321201&sectionId=36213&sectionno=25&orderno=25&orgactid=AC_CEN_24_32_00002_195649_1517807321201
obj_root_law_sections_25_content:
  string
  line `All members and officers of a Board`
  line `shall, when acting or purporting to act in pursuance of any of the provisions of this Act, be deemed to be`
  line `public servants within the meaning of section 21 of the Indian Penal Code (45 of 1860).`
obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_26:
  sectionId (36214)
  sectionNo (26)
  orderNo 26
  title `Protection of action taken in good faith.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_26_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_24_32_00002_195649_1517807321201&sectionId=36214&sectionno=26&orderno=26&orgactid=AC_CEN_24_32_00002_195649_1517807321201
obj_root_law_sections_26_content:
  string
  line `No suit or other legal proceeding shall lie against any`
  line `member or officer of a Board in respect of anything which is in good faith done or intended to be done in`
  line `pursuance of this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_27:
  sectionId (36215)
  sectionNo (27)
  orderNo 27
  title `Dissolution of Board and transfer of assets and liabilities.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_27_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_24_32_00002_195649_1517807321201&sectionId=36215&sectionno=27&orderno=27&orgactid=AC_CEN_24_32_00002_195649_1517807321201
obj_root_law_sections_27_content:
  string
  line `(1) When the Central Government`
  line `is of opinion that a Board has performed its functions under this Act, the Central Government, after`
  line `consultation with the Governments interested, may, by notification in the Official Gazette, declare that the`
  line `Board shall be dissolved from such date as may be specified in this behalf in such notification; and the`
  line `Board shall be deemed to have been dissolved accordingly.`
  line
  line `(2) On the dissolution of the Board by a notification under sub-section (1),--`
  line
  line `(a) all properties, funds and dues which are vested in, or realisable by, the Board shall vest in, and`
  line `be reliable by, such Government or authority as may be specified in the said notification; and`
  line
  line `(b) all liabilities which are enforceable against the Board shall be enforceable only against the`
  line `Government or authority specified in the said notification.`
obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_28:
  sectionId (36216)
  sectionNo (28)
  orderNo 28
  title `Power to make rules.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_28_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 4 of 1986, s. 2 and the Schedule, for sub-section (3) (w.e.f. 15-5-1986).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_24_32_00002_195649_1517807321201&sectionId=36216&sectionno=28&orderno=28&orgactid=AC_CEN_24_32_00002_195649_1517807321201
obj_root_law_sections_28_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette,`
  line `make rules to carry out the purposes of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) In particular, and without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing power, such rules may`
  line `provide for all or any of the following matters, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) the salaries, allowances and conditions of service of members of the Board;`
  line
  line `(b) the matters in respect of which a Board may tender advice to the Governments interested`
  line `under sub-clause (viii) of clause (a) of section 13;`
  line
  line `(c) the matters in respect of which the Board may require a Government interested to furnish`
  line information;
  line
  line `(d) the manner in which the Central Government may assist the Governments interested to`
  line `execute any scheme prepared by the Board;`
  line
  line `(e) the form in which, and the time within which, the budget and annual report of the Board may`
  line `be prepared and forwarded to the Central Government and the Governments interested;`
  line
  line `(f) the form and manner in which the accounts of the Board may be maintained, and the time at`
  line `which, and the manner in which, such accounts may be audited;`
  line
  line `(g) the returns and information which the Board may be required to furnish to the Central`
  line Government;
  line
  line `(h) the form and manner in which a dispute may be referred to arbitration under this Act;`
  line
  line `(i) the procedure to be followed in arbitration proceedings under this Act;`
  line
  line `(j) the manner of recruitment of the officers of a Board and the terms and conditions of service of`
  line `such officers;`
  line
  line `(k) any other matter which has to be, or may be prescribed;`
  line
  line `^1[(3) Every rule made under this section shall be laid, as soon as may be after it is made, before each`
  line `House of Parliament, while it is in session, for a total period of thirty days which may be comprised in`
  line `one session or in two or more successive sessions, and if, before the expiry of the session immediately`
  line `following the session or the successive sessions aforesaid, both Houses agree in making any modification`
  line `in the rule or both Houses agree that the rule should not be made, the rule shall thereafter have effect only`
  line `in such modified form or be of no effect, as the case may be; so, however, that any such modification or`
  line `annulment shall be without prejudice to the validity of anything previously done under that rule.]`
obj_root_law_sections_29:
  sectionId (36217)
  sectionNo (29)
  orderNo 29
  title `Power to make regulations.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_29_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_24_32_00002_195649_1517807321201&sectionId=36217&sectionno=29&orderno=29&orgactid=AC_CEN_24_32_00002_195649_1517807321201
obj_root_law_sections_29_content:
  string
  line `^1[(1)] The Board may, with the previous approval of the Central`
  line `Government, by notification in the Gazette of India, make regulations, not inconsistent with this Act or`
  line `the rules made thereunder--`
  line
  line `(a) regulating the meetings of the Board and the procedure for conducting business thereat;`
  line
  line `(b) regulating the manner in which, and the purposes for which, advisory committees may be`
  line appointed;
  line
  line `(c) regulating the manner in which and the purposes for which persons may be associated with`
  line `the Board under section 11;`
  line
  line `(d) determining the terms and conditions of service of the members of advisory committees, of`
  line `persons associated with the Board under section 11 and of all officers appointed by the Board.`
  line
  line `^2[(2) Every regulation made under this section shall be laid, as soon as may be after it is made, before`
  line `each House of Parliament, while it is in session, for a total period of thirty days which may be comprised`
  line `in one session or in two or more successive sessions, and if, before the expiry of the session immediately`
  line `following the session or the successive sessions aforesaid, both Houses agree in making any modification`
  line `in the regulation or both Houses agree that the regulation should not be made, the regulation shall`
  line `thereafter have effect only in such modified form or be of no effect, as the case may be; so, however, that`
  line `any such modification or annulment shall be without prejudice to the validity of anything previously done`
  line `under that regulation.]`
obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Section 29 renumbered as sub-section (1) of that section by s. 2 and the Schedule, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-10-1984).`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by s. 2 and the Schedule, ibid. (w.e.f. 15-5-1986).`
obj_root_law_translations:
  hi obj_root_law_translations_hi
